Frequently Asked Questions about Intercontinental Danang Sun Peninsula Resort
Which popular attractions are close to Intercontinental Danang Sun Peninsula Resort?
Nearby attractions include Da Nang Local Tours by Hung Le Travel (3.1 miles), 3D Museum Art in Paradise Danang (4.5 miles), and Lady Buddha (2.5 miles).
See all nearby attractions.
What are some of the property amenities at Intercontinental Danang Sun Peninsula Resort?
Some of the more popular amenities offered include free wifi, a pool, and an on-site restaurant.
See all property amenities.
Which room amenities are available at Intercontinental Danang Sun Peninsula Resort?
Top room amenities include a minibar, air conditioning, and a flat screen TV.
See all room amenities.
What food & drink options are available at Intercontinental Danang Sun Peninsula Resort?
Guests can enjoy an on-site restaurant, a lounge, and a poolside bar during their stay.
Learn more.
Is parking available at Intercontinental Danang Sun Peninsula Resort?
Yes, free parking, a parking garage, and secured parking are available to guests.
What are some restaurants close to Intercontinental Danang Sun Peninsula Resort?
Conveniently located restaurants include Citron Restaurant, Barefoot restaurant, and La Maison 1888.
See all nearby restaurants.
Are there opportunities to exercise at Intercontinental Danang Sun Peninsula Resort?
Yes, guests have access to a pool, a fitness center, and fitness classes during their stay.
Does Intercontinental Danang Sun Peninsula Resort have airport transportation?
Yes, Intercontinental Danang Sun Peninsula Resort offers airport transportation for guests. We recommend calling ahead to confirm details.
Are any cleaning services offered at Intercontinental Danang Sun Peninsula Resort?
Yes, dry cleaning and laundry service are offered to guests.
Does Intercontinental Danang Sun Peninsula Resort offer any business services?
Yes, it conveniently offers a business center, meeting rooms, and a banquet room.
Which languages are spoken by the staff at Intercontinental Danang Sun Peninsula Resort?
The staff speaks multiple languages, including English, French, Russian, Chinese, Japanese, Vietnamese, and Korean.
Want more?
